Document: VisibleOnScreenNotifier2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_visibleonscreennotifier2d.rst  
Summary: Properties for defining the bounding rectangle and its visibility in the editor.  

rect (Rect2): The VisibleOnScreenNotifier2D's bounding rectangle. Default: Rect2(-10, -10, 20, 20). Method: set_rect(value: Rect2) → void. Method: get_rect() → Rect2.  

show_rect (bool): If true, shows the rectangle area of rect in the editor with a translucent magenta fill. Unlike changing the visibility of the VisibleOnScreenNotifier2D, this does not affect the screen culling detection. Default: true. Method: set_show_rect(value: bool) → void. Method: is_showing_rect() → bool. Note: Editor visualization does not impact screen culling logic.
---CHUNK---
Document: VisibleOnScreenNotifier2D
Path: godot/classes/class_visibleonscreennotifier2d.rst
Summary: Describes the is_on_screen() method which checks if the node's bounding rectangle is visible on the screen.

Method: is_on_screen() → bool
If true, the bounding rectangle is on the screen.

Note: It takes one frame for the VisibleOnScreenNotifier2D's visibility to be determined once added to the scene tree, so this method will always return false right after it is instantiated, before the draw pass.